-- Insurers to face record payout from quake: Japan insurance assoc
-- 
-- Thu Mar 17, 2011 5:33am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/17/us-japan-quake-insurance-idUSTRE72G1EL20110317

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Insurers will likely face the biggest-ever payout from last week's massive earthquake that hit northeastern Japan, the chairman of the general insurance association of Japan said on Thursday. 

 But the payout is unlikely to damage nonlife insurers' financial health, Hisahito Suzuki said in a statement. (Reporting by  Mariko Katsumura ; Editing by  Nathan Layne )